ABOUT:
Brown Spot is a fungal disease caused by Bipolaris oryzae. It commonly appears during nutrient stress and affects seedlings and mature plants.

SYMPTOMS:
Brown circular spots on leaves
Yellow halo around lesions
Leaf drying in severe infection
Reduced seedling vigor

PREVENTION:
Apply balanced fertilizers, especially Nitrogen
Improve soil drainage
Use disease-free seeds
Apply fungicides if infection is severe
